&gt;  That&#39;s what mine did when I cut the green wire. So I patched that, flipped the board over so I could see which wire the mute was on, it was a blue wire, then miss counted, cut the worng wire again, patched that, then unsoldered the right one. You might make sure none of the pins shorted. 
